DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);


install_problem_grader(~~&std_problem_grader);
TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;
$showPartialCredit = 0;

$base = random(5.1,12.9,0.2);

$a = int(100000*log(2)/(log($base)))/100000;




TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 




Let 
\[L(x) = \hbox{log}_a(x)\]
where we don't know the base \(a\).  However,
we do know that 

\[L(2) = $a.\]



$BR

Then \(a= \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}.
EOT
ANS(num_cmp($base));


TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR $BBOLD Hint:$EBOLD Solve the equation \(a^{$a} = 2\).
EOT

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT')); 
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD  We need to solve the equation
\[a^{$a}  = 2.\]  Taking both sides to the power \(1/$a\) gives
\[a = 2^{1/$a} \approx $base.\]
EOT





ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
